cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on a two-tier heterogeneous cellular network and its performance analysis in terms of delivery rate. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the impact of cache size and rate splitting on the performance of small cells, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with the deployment of cache-enabled small cells and their inter-tier and intra-tier dependence, which involves distributed computing concepts. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of a complex system (two-tier HCN) and proposes adjustments for rate fairness, which involves systems and control concepts. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the delivery rate of multimedia content in a heterogeneous network, which involves multimedia concepts.
